#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-composition-patterns/rules/patterns-explicit-variants.md
M|rules|title: Create Explicit Component Variants
M|rules|impact: MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: self-documenting code, no hidden conditionals
M|rules|tags: composition, variants, architecture
M|rules|Instead of one component with many boolean props, create explicit variant
M|rules|components. Each variant composes the pieces it needs. The code documents
M|rules|itself.
M|rules|**Incorrect (one component, many modes):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|// What does this component actually render?
M|rules|<Composer
M|rules|isThread
M|rules|isEditing={false}
M|rules|channelId='abc'
M|rules|showAttachments
M|rules|showFormatting={false}
M|rules|/>
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (explicit variants):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|// Immediately clear what this renders
M|rules|<ThreadComposer channelId="abc" />
M|rules|// Or
M|rules|<EditMessageComposer messageId="xyz" />
M|rules|// Or
M|rules|<ForwardMessageComposer messageId="123" />
M|rules|```
M|rules|Each implementation is unique, explicit and self-contained. Yet they can each
M|rules|use shared parts.
M|rules|**Implementation:**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function ThreadComposer({ channelId }: { channelId: string }) {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<ThreadProvider channelId={channelId}>
M|rules|<Composer.Frame>
M|rules|<Composer.Input />
M|rules|<AlsoSendToChannelField channelId={channelId} />
M|rules|<Composer.Footer>
M|rules|<Composer.Formatting />
M|rules|<Composer.Emojis />
M|rules|<Composer.Submit />
M|rules|</Composer.Footer>
M|rules|</Composer.Frame>
M|rules|</ThreadProvider>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|function EditMessageComposer({ messageId }: { messageId: string }) {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<EditMessageProvider messageId={messageId}>
M|rules|<Composer.Frame>
M|rules|<Composer.Input />
M|rules|<Composer.Footer>
M|rules|<Composer.Formatting />
M|rules|<Composer.Emojis />
M|rules|<Composer.CancelEdit />
M|rules|<Composer.SaveEdit />
M|rules|</Composer.Footer>
M|rules|</Composer.Frame>
M|rules|</EditMessageProvider>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|function ForwardMessageComposer({ messageId }: { messageId: string }) {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<ForwardMessageProvider messageId={messageId}>
M|rules|<Composer.Frame>
M|rules|<Composer.Input placeholder="Add a message, if you'd like." />
M|rules|<Composer.Footer>
M|rules|<Composer.Formatting />
M|rules|<Composer.Emojis />
M|rules|<Composer.Mentions />
M|rules|</Composer.Footer>
M|rules|</Composer.Frame>
M|rules|</ForwardMessageProvider>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|Each variant is explicit about:
M|rules|- What provider/state it uses
M|rules|- What UI elements it includes
M|rules|- What actions are available
M|rules|No boolean prop combinations to reason about. No impossible states.